1
00:00:11,178 --> 00:00:15,182
T'POL: SCIENCE OFFICER'S LOG,
AUGUST 14, 2152.

2
00:00:15,182 --> 00:00:19,227
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> REMAINS ON COURSE
FOR THE TRINARY SYSTEM.

3
00:00:19,227 --> 00:00:21,229
I'VE TRANSMITTED
A DISTRESS CALL,

4
00:00:21,229 --> 00:00:25,108
BUT THE NEAREST VULCAN SHIP
IS MORE THAN NINE DAYS AWAY.

5
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:29,029
BY THE TIME THEY ARRIVE, THEY
MAY ONLY FIND DEBRIS, IF THAT.

6
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:31,991
EVEN IF<i> ENTERPRISE</i> MAKES IT
PAST THE BLACK HOLE

7
00:00:31,991 --> 00:00:33,784
WITHOUT BEING DESTROYED,

8
00:00:33,784 --> 00:00:37,287
IT SEEMS LIKELY
THE CREW WON'T SURVIVE.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,462
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

10
00:00:45,462 --> 00:00:48,674
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

11
00:00:48,674 --> 00:00:52,553
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

12
00:00:52,553 --> 00:00:56,097
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

13
00:00:56,097 --> 00:01:00,644
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

14
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:04,314
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

15
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:08,318
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

16
00:01:08,318 --> 00:01:11,196
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

17
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:13,908
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

18
00:01:13,908 --> 00:01:16,451
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

19
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:19,788
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

20
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:24,668
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

21
00:01:24,668 --> 00:01:27,046
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

22
00:01:27,046 --> 00:01:31,717
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

23
00:01:31,717 --> 00:01:34,553
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

24
00:01:34,553 --> 00:01:40,267
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

25
00:01:40,267 --> 00:01:42,269
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

26
00:01:42,269 --> 00:01:44,563
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

27
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:48,025
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

28
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:52,863
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

29
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:06,627
I'M CONTINUING MY ANALYSIS

30
00:02:06,627 --> 00:02:09,170
OF THE CONDITION
THAT'S STRICKEN THE CREW.

31
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:12,382
WITHOUT DR. PHLOX'S
ASSISTANCE,

32
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:17,471
I'M NOT HOPEFUL ABOUT
REVERSING ITS EFFECTS.

33
00:02:17,471 --> 00:02:19,723
I'M DOCUMENTING MY FINDINGS
SO THAT STARFLEET

34
00:02:19,723 --> 00:02:23,435
WILL AT LEAST HAVE A RECORD
OF WHAT HAPPENED.

35
00:02:23,435 --> 00:02:25,771
THE SYMPTOMS BEGAN NOT LONG

36
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:29,817
AFTER WE SET A COURSE
FOR THE TRINARY SYSTEM.

37
00:02:29,817 --> 00:02:32,486
THAT WAS NEARLY TWO DAYS AGO.

38
00:02:34,279 --> 00:02:36,115
ARCHER: YOU'RE SURE
IT'S A BLACK HOLE?

39
00:02:36,115 --> 00:02:38,117
T'POL: A CLASS-4.

40
00:02:38,117 --> 00:02:40,494
TUCKER: ACCORDING
TO THE VULCAN STARCHARTS,

41
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:43,580
YOUR PEOPLE HAVE SURVEYED
MORE THAN 2,000 OF THESE THINGS.

42
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:46,667
T'POL: THAT'S CORRECT,
BUT NONE OF THEM

43
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,711
WERE PART OF A TRINARY
STAR SYSTEM.

44
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,672
ARCHER: HOW CLOSE CAN WE GET?

45
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:54,883
T'POL: THE GRAVITATIONAL SHEAR
BETWEEN THE STARS IS EXTREME.

46
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:57,344
WE'D HAVE TO DROP TO IMPULSE,
BUT WE SHOULD BE ABLE

47
00:02:57,344 --> 00:03:00,555
TO APPROACH TO WITHIN
5 MILLION KILOMETERS.

48
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:04,101
CLOSE ENOUGH TO GET
SOME NICE PICTURES.

49
00:03:04,101 --> 00:03:07,562
HOW LONG WOULD IT TAKE
TO REACH THE SYSTEM AT IMPULSE?

50
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,188
TWO DAYS.

51
00:03:09,188 --> 00:03:10,816
SET A COURSE.

52
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:14,444
TRIP.

53
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:18,615
IF YOU'VE GOT SOME FREE TIME,

54
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:21,035
I'D LOVE IT IF YOU'D TAKE
A LOOK AT MY CHAIR.

55
00:03:21,035 --> 00:03:22,369
SIR?

56
00:03:22,369 --> 00:03:24,121
THE CAPTAIN'S CHAIR.

57
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:27,499
WHAT ABOUT IT?

58
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:29,543
YOU MAY HAVE NOTICED

59
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:32,629
THAT I DON'T SIT
IN IT VERY MUCH.

60
00:03:32,629 --> 00:03:34,589
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

61
00:03:34,589 --> 00:03:36,633
IT'S UNCOMFORTABLE.

62
00:03:36,633 --> 00:03:38,552
WHEN I LEAN BACK,

63
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,638
I FEEL LIKE I'M ABOUT
TO SLIDE OUT OF IT.

64
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:44,224
I HAVE TO SORT OF...

65
00:03:44,224 --> 00:03:46,185
PERCH ON THE EDGE.

66
00:03:46,185 --> 00:03:50,064
I ALWAYS ASSUMED IT WAS
THE BEST SEAT IN THE HOUSE.

67
00:03:50,064 --> 00:03:52,066
TAKE A LOOK AT IT FOR ME?

68
00:03:52,066 --> 00:03:54,234
I WAS GONNA PURGE
THE IMPULSE MANIFOLDS.

69
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:57,320
THE CHAIR FIRST,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

70
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,947
AYE, AYE, SIR.

71
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:00,240
HMM.

72
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:02,743
[ BEEPING ]

73
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:03,994
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

74
00:04:03,994 --> 00:04:06,580
COME IN.

75
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,623
-GOOD MORNING.
-MORNING.

76
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:10,209
AM I INTERRUPTING?

77
00:04:10,209 --> 00:04:13,294
NO, NO, JUST THINKING
ABOUT SOMETHING.

78
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:15,172
TODAY'S DUTY ROSTER.

79
00:04:15,172 --> 00:04:16,464
THANKS.

80
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:18,759
LIEUTENANT REED HAS
A NEW SECURITY PROTOCOL

81
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,052
HE'D LIKE TO DISCUSS WITH YOU.

82
00:04:20,052 --> 00:04:23,805
I'LL DROP BY THE ARMORY.
ANYTHING ELSE?

83
00:04:23,805 --> 00:04:27,059
CHEF DIDN'T REPORT FOR DUTY
THIS MORNING. HE'S ILL.

84
00:04:27,059 --> 00:04:28,769
IS IT SERIOUS?

85
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:30,812
T'POL: DR. PHLOX SAID
IT'S A SIMPLE VIRUS.

86
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:32,773
HE SHOULD BE FINE
AFTER A FEW DAYS' REST.

87
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:35,650
ENSIGN SATO HAS OFFERED
TO TAKE CHARGE OF THE MESS HALL.

88
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,028
APPARENTLY, SHE SPENDS SOME
OF HER FREE TIME IN THE GALLEY

89
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:41,322
AND IS EAGER FOR AN OPPORTUNITY
TO COOK FOR THE CREW.

90
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:45,160
IF IT'S ALL RIGHT WITH CHEF.

91
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,204
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION.

92
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:52,459
I RECEIVED A MANUSCRIPT
FROM EARTH...

93
00:04:52,459 --> 00:04:54,711
A BIOGRAPHY OF MY FATHER.

94
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:58,715
I HAVE BEEN ASKED
TO WRITE THE PREFACE.

95
00:05:00,717 --> 00:05:03,386
WOULD YOU MIND READING IT
WHEN I'M DONE?

96
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,180
I'D BE HAPPY TO.

97
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:08,558
IF I CAN EVER GET IT FINISHED.

98
00:05:08,558 --> 00:05:11,186
I'VE BEEN PUTTING IT OFF
FOR WEEKS.

99
00:05:11,186 --> 00:05:14,773
THE NEXT TWO DAYS SHOULD PROVIDE
YOU WITH AMPLE OPPORTUNITY.

100
00:05:14,773 --> 00:05:17,818
IT'S NOT THAT
I HAVEN'T HAD THE TIME.

101
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:20,070
THEY ONLY ASKED FOR A PAGE.

102
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:25,075
HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO SUM UP
MY FATHER'S LIFE IN A PAGE?

103
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:28,620
WOULD HAVE BEEN EASIER IF THEY'D
ASKED ME TO WRITE THE BOOK.

104
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:33,041
PERHAPS, BY FOCUSING
ON ONE INCIDENT, A SINGLE EVENT

105
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:36,086
THAT EXEMPLIFIES YOUR
RELATIONSHIP WITH YOUR FATHER,

106
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:39,173
YOU'LL BE ABLE
TO CONDENSE YOUR THOUGHTS.

107
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:41,175
LOGICAL APPROACH.

108
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:47,097
MAYBE...YOU'D LIKE
TO WRITE IT FOR ME?

109
00:05:47,097 --> 00:05:50,017
I AM HARDLY QUALIFIED.

110
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,487
CHEF WAS PLANNING TO MAKE
FRIED CHICKEN TONIGHT

111
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:04,948
WITH SCALLOPED POTATOES
AND SOME OF THE MINARAN SPINACH

112
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:06,325
WE PICKED UP ON RISA.

113
00:06:06,325 --> 00:06:07,784
THE ORANGE SPINACH?

114
00:06:07,784 --> 00:06:09,452
HE'S CONVINCED THERE'S A WAY
TO MAKE IT EDIBLE.

115
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,538
WHY DON'T WE LET HIM TACKLE THAT
WHEN HE GETS BACK?

116
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,165
I HAVE SOMETHING ELSE IN MIND.

117
00:06:13,165 --> 00:06:15,959
IT'S ONE OF MY GRANDMOTHER'S
SPECIALTIES.

118
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:18,837
THE RECIPE'S BEEN PASSED DOWN
FOR GENERATIONS.

119
00:06:18,837 --> 00:06:20,421
I'LL NEED A TRANSLATION

120
00:06:20,421 --> 00:06:22,465
BEFORE I CAN PROGRAM
THE PROTEIN RESEQUENCER.

121
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:24,009
OH, NO.

122
00:06:24,009 --> 00:06:27,304
YOU CAN RESEQUENCE ALL THE
CHICKEN AND POTATOES YOU WANT,

123
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:31,016
BUT I AM MAKING THIS
FROM SCRATCH.

124
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:44,112
ENSIGN...

125
00:06:44,112 --> 00:06:46,447
IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN DO FOR YOU?

126
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:50,202
I'VE GOT A LITTLE HEADACHE --
NOTHING SERIOUS.

127
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,872
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME HAVE
A LOOK?

128
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:56,250
I WAS HOPING YOU COULD
JUST GIVE ME SOMETHING.

129
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:57,751
I'M RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF UPGRADING

130
00:06:57,751 --> 00:06:59,127
THE NAVIGATION SENSORS.

131
00:06:59,127 --> 00:07:01,046
IT WOULD BE IRRESPONSIBLE
TO DISPENSE MEDICATION

132
00:07:01,046 --> 00:07:02,672
WITHOUT EXAMINING YOU FIRST.

133
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,674
HMM? PLEASE.

134
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:07,135
ANY OTHER SYMPTOMS --

135
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:09,096
DIZZINESS, BLURRED VISION?

136
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:10,638
-NO.
-AH.

137
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:12,599
HOW LONG HAVE YOU HAD IT?

138
00:07:12,599 --> 00:07:14,684
A COUPLE OF DAYS, ON AND OFF.

139
00:07:14,684 --> 00:07:15,977
WELL, I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO HAVE YOU

140
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:18,355
DROP BY SICK BAY,
IN ANY CASE, HMM?

141
00:07:18,355 --> 00:07:21,066
TO SEE IF YOU'VE
HAD ANY PROBLEMS

142
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:22,609
SINCE I REMOVED
THE NEURAL IMPLANTS

143
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:24,319
YOU RECEIVED
AT THE REPAIR STATION.

144
00:07:24,319 --> 00:07:27,072
YOU THINK IT COULD HAVE
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THAT?

145
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:30,075
PHLOX: OH, I NEVER
RULE OUT ANYTHING.

146
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:34,121
THEN AGAIN, IT COULD BE AS
INNOCUOUS AS MUSCULAR TENSION.

147
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:36,415
ON THE OTHER HAND,

148
00:07:36,415 --> 00:07:41,669
TERRELLIAN PLAGUE STARTS OUT
WITH A SIMPLE HEADACHE...

149
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:46,049
AND THEN ALL MANNER
OF NASTY THINGS BEGIN TO HAPPEN.

150
00:07:46,049 --> 00:07:47,592
[ CHUCKLES ]

151
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,469
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

152
00:07:55,350 --> 00:07:58,061
[ POWER TOOL WHIRRING ]

153
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:01,064
COMMANDER.

154
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:03,358
[ WHIRRING CONTINUES ]

155
00:08:06,945 --> 00:08:08,989
T'POL: COMMANDER.

156
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:11,532
PUSH IT FORWARD.

157
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:13,618
THAT'S GOOD.
HOLD IT THERE.

158
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:15,203
COMMANDER!

159
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:16,413
[ WHIRRING STOPS ]

160
00:08:16,413 --> 00:08:18,290
PERHAPS YOU COULD
FINISH THAT LATER.

161
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,626
THIS MAY NOT BE AS GLAMOROUS
AS A BLACK HOLE,

162
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:23,628
BUT THE CAPTAIN GAVE ME
AN ORDER.

163
00:08:23,628 --> 00:08:25,880
HE ALSO REQUESTED DETAILED
SENSOR READINGS

164
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,674
OF THIS TRINARY SYSTEM.

165
00:08:27,674 --> 00:08:30,551
I THOUGHT VULCANS HAD ALL THIS
MENTAL FOCUS AND DISCIPLINE.

166
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,764
WE ALSO HAVE SENSITIVE HEARING.

167
00:08:36,350 --> 00:08:38,018
HMM.

168
00:08:39,560 --> 00:08:41,396
[ WHIRRING RESUMES ]

169
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:48,487
I'LL BE IN MY QUARTERS.

170
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,573
WE'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN WE'RE DONE.

171
00:08:55,369 --> 00:08:57,787
REED: KEEP THOSE TARGET
DISCRIMINATORS ALIGNED.

172
00:08:57,787 --> 00:08:59,831
WE DON'T WANT A TORPEDO
MISTAKING ONE

173
00:08:59,831 --> 00:09:02,501
OF OUR OWN NACELLES
FOR AN ENEMY VESSEL.

174
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,754
ARCHER: YOU ASKED
TO SEE ME, MALCOLM?

175
00:09:06,754 --> 00:09:08,673
OH, I WOULD HAVE COME
TO YOU, CAPTAIN.

176
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:11,259
IT'S NO PROBLEM.
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

177
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:17,557
I'VE BEEN REVIEWING OUR
ENCOUNTERS WITH HOSTILE SPECIES.

178
00:09:17,557 --> 00:09:20,227
THE CREW'S RESPONSE
HAS BEEN ADMIRABLE,

179
00:09:20,227 --> 00:09:23,063
BUT I FEEL WE CAN
DO BETTER, SIR.

180
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:25,815
AND YOU HAVE A PROPOSAL?

181
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:29,027
I'VE BEEN THINKING ABOUT
A SHIPWIDE EMERGENCY ALERT,

182
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:31,071
SOMETHING
A BIT MORE COMPREHENSIVE

183
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:32,739
THAN "BATTLE STATIONS."

184
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:36,451
WE'RE TAKING FAR TOO LONG
TO REACT TO POTENTIAL THREATS.

185
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:39,871
WITH A SINGLE ORDER FROM YOU
OR AN IMPACT TO THE HULL,

186
00:09:39,871 --> 00:09:42,665
THE PLATING COULD BE POLARIZED,
WEAPONS BROUGHT ONLINE,

187
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:44,251
CRITICAL SYSTEMS SECURED --

188
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:46,461
I APPRECIATE YOUR CONCERN,
MALCOLM,

189
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:48,338
BUT THIS ISN'T A WARSHIP.

190
00:09:48,338 --> 00:09:51,007
WELL, THAT'S OBVIOUS, SIR.

191
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:54,469
DURING OUR LAST RUN-IN
WITH THE SULIBAN,

192
00:09:54,469 --> 00:09:59,140
WE WERE...UNPREPARED
FOR THEIR BOARDING PARTIES.

193
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,725
WHEN THE MAZARITES ATTACKED,

194
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,019
THEY DISABLED OUR AFT SENSORS
WITH THEIR FIRST SHOT.

195
00:10:03,019 --> 00:10:04,645
THE LIST GOES ON.

196
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:06,314
I CAN SEE THAT.

197
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:13,696
RUN THIS BY THE SENIOR OFFICERS,

198
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:17,784
GET SOME FEEDBACK,
AND WE'LL TALK AGAIN.

199
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:20,203
YES, SIR.

200
00:10:20,203 --> 00:10:22,581
ARCHER: AND MALCOLM...

201
00:10:22,581 --> 00:10:25,292
DON'T CALL IT "BATTLE STATIONS."

202
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,836
THINK OF SOMETHING
LESS AGGRESSIVE.

203
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,853
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

204
00:10:45,853 --> 00:10:47,981
-HOW IS IT?
-REALLY GOOD. IT'S GREAT.

205
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:50,442
"CONDITION RED"?

206
00:10:50,442 --> 00:10:52,026
HUH?

207
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:55,196
WHAT ABOUT "CONDITION RED"
FOR THE NEW SECURITY PROTOCOL?

208
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:57,865
WHY DON'T YOU JUST CALL IT
"SECURITY PROTOCOL"?

209
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,701
WELL, THAT'S NOT VERY DYNAMIC.

210
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:04,539
DO YOU THINK
A CUP HOLDER'S TOO MUCH?

211
00:11:04,539 --> 00:11:06,458
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

212
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:07,834
FOR THE CAPTAIN'S CHAIR.

213
00:11:07,834 --> 00:11:09,419
HE JUST WANTED
THE SEAT ADJUSTED,

214
00:11:09,419 --> 00:11:12,172
BUT I FIGURED, AS LONG
AS I'M WORKING ON IT...

215
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:15,216
JUST WHAT THE CAPTAIN NEEDS
IN A CRISIS --

216
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,469
A PLACE TO REST HIS BEVERAGE.

217
00:11:17,469 --> 00:11:20,096
I'M ALSO UPGRADING
THE STATUS DISPLAYS.

218
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:23,308
HE'LL BE ABLE TO ACCESS
TACTICAL DATA FROM THE ARMREST.

219
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:26,269
IF YOU REALLY WANT TO IMPROVE
TACTICAL READINESS,

220
00:11:26,269 --> 00:11:29,105
WHY DON'T YOU HELP ME
WITH THIS PROTOCOL?

221
00:11:30,315 --> 00:11:32,359
I'M A LITTLE BUSY
RIGHT NOW, MALCOLM.

222
00:11:32,359 --> 00:11:34,777
IT'S A<i> CHAIR.</i>

223
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:37,905
IT'S THE<i> CAPTAIN'S</i> CHAIR.

224
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:42,536
IT'S JUST AS IMPORTANT
AS YOUR...REED ALERT.

225
00:11:42,536 --> 00:11:45,622
"REED ALERT"?
THAT'S NOT BAD.

226
00:11:45,622 --> 00:11:48,208
ENJOYING YOUR LUNCH?

227
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:50,793
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
YEAH.

228
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:52,587
THANKS. IT WAS,
UH, TERRIFIC.

229
00:11:52,587 --> 00:11:54,214
HOSHI: IT'S CALLED "ODEN."

230
00:11:54,214 --> 00:11:57,050
EVERY JAPANESE FAMILY HAS
THEIR OWN WAY OF PREPARING IT.

231
00:11:58,635 --> 00:12:01,221
WELL, IT SEEMS TO BE A BIG HIT.

232
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:02,472
CONGRATULATIONS.

233
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:03,890
THANK YOU.

234
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,601
LIEUTENANT,
YOU BARELY TOUCHED YOURS.

235
00:12:06,601 --> 00:12:08,019
UH, IT WAS LOVELY.

236
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:09,479
I'LL GET YOU A FRESH BOWL.

237
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:10,771
THAT'S NOT NECESSARY.

238
00:12:10,771 --> 00:12:12,023
HOSHI: IT'S NO PROBLEM.

239
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:14,568
PLEASE. NOT HUNGRY.

240
00:12:14,568 --> 00:12:17,862
ARE YOU SURE THERE'S
NOTHING WRONG WITH IT?

241
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:23,076
WELL...IT WAS A BIT SALTY.

242
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:24,743
SALTY?

243
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:32,919
OH, IT TASTES FINE.

244
00:12:34,504 --> 00:12:36,256
WELL, IT JUST MUST BE ME, THEN.

245
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:38,757
REED: EVERYBODY ELSE SEEMS
TO BE ENJOYING IT.

246
00:12:43,221 --> 00:12:44,847
HOW MUCH LONGER
IS THIS GOING TO TAKE?

247
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:46,140
-THAT DEPENDS.
-ON WHAT?

248
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,559
HOLD STILL, ENSIGN.

249
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:49,894
I HAVE TO GET BACK
TO THE BRIDGE.

250
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,939
WELL, I'M AFRAID YOU WON'T BE
RETURNING TO DUTY TODAY.

251
00:12:52,939 --> 00:12:54,524
THE CAPTAIN NEEDS
THOSE UPGRADES, DOCTOR.

252
00:12:54,524 --> 00:12:56,109
WHEN IT COMES
TO MEDICAL MATTERS,

253
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:57,736
MY AUTHORITY OVERRIDES
THE CAPTAIN'S.

254
00:12:57,736 --> 00:12:59,362
I'M KEEPING YOU OVERNIGHT
FOR OBSERVATION.

255
00:12:59,362 --> 00:13:01,030
BUT YOUR SCANS
DIDN'T SHOW ANYTHING.

256
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,657
THAT'S WHAT CONCERNS ME.

257
00:13:02,657 --> 00:13:04,909
WHATEVER'S AFFLICTING YOU
MAY BE LAYING DORMANT.

258
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,953
I'M GOING TO RUN
A FULL BIOMOLECULAR SCAN

259
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:09,706
TO SEE IF WE CAN FIND
WHERE IT'S HIDING.

260
00:13:09,706 --> 00:13:12,667
NOW, LIE...BACK

261
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:14,711
AND DON'T MOVE.

262
00:13:14,711 --> 00:13:16,379
[ SIGHS ]

263
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:28,349
WHEN I WAS
ABOUT EIGHT YEARS OLD,

264
00:13:28,349 --> 00:13:30,310
MY FATHER TOOK ME ON A TOUR

265
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:34,397
OF THE WARP 5 FACILITY
OUTSIDE OF BOZEMAN, MONTANA.

266
00:13:35,732 --> 00:13:38,318
HE INTRODUCED ME
TO THE PEOPLE HE WORKED WITH,

267
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:43,323
SCIENTISTS WITH NAMES LIKE...
TASAKI AND COCHRANE.

268
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:45,533
AT THE TIME, I DIDN'T REALIZE

269
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,744
THE -- THE SIGNIFICANCE
OF THOSE NAMES

270
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,705
OR THE...THE SIGNIFICANCE

271
00:13:50,705 --> 00:13:53,750
OF...MY FATHER'S WORK.

272
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,585
[ BARKS ]
COMPUTER, PAUSE.

273
00:13:55,585 --> 00:13:57,420
I'LL FEED YOU IN A MINUTE.

274
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,802
COMPUTER, RESUME RECORDING.
[ BEEPS ]

275
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:07,013
IN A WAY...

276
00:14:07,013 --> 00:14:11,017
CREATING A STABLE WARP FIELD...

277
00:14:11,017 --> 00:14:14,020
MIRRORED THE...

278
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:17,649
THE F-FLUX OF EMOTIONS...

279
00:14:17,649 --> 00:14:20,485
MY...FATHER FELT

280
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:22,903
WHEN HE...

281
00:14:22,903 --> 00:14:25,532
EMBARKED ON...

282
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:27,534
COMPUTER, PAUSE.
[ BEEPS ]

283
00:14:27,534 --> 00:14:30,578
DELETE THE LAST PARAGRAPH.
HELL, DELETE THE WHOLE THING.

284
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:32,288
[ BARKS ]
QUIET.

285
00:14:47,178 --> 00:14:48,680
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

286
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,431
COME IN.

287
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:56,771
HERE'S YOUR SENSOR INTERFACE.

288
00:14:56,771 --> 00:14:59,399
WHAT'S THE EMERGENCY?

289
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:02,402
THIS TRINARY SYSTEM IS EMITTING
SOME UNUSUAL RADIATION.

290
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:04,111
I'M TRYING TO IDENTIFY IT.

291
00:15:04,111 --> 00:15:06,573
YOU DRAGGED ME UP HERE

292
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:09,158
SO YOU COULD IDENTIFY RADIATION?

293
00:15:09,158 --> 00:15:10,827
T'POL: CORRECT.

294
00:15:10,827 --> 00:15:12,495
YOU SAID IT WAS URGENT.

295
00:15:12,495 --> 00:15:14,581
I SAID IT WAS IMPORTANT.

296
00:15:14,581 --> 00:15:17,166
I GET IT.

297
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:19,794
YOU'RE PAYING ME BACK,

298
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:21,713
MAKING ME JUMP
THROUGH HOOPS BECAUSE I WAS

299
00:15:21,713 --> 00:15:24,090
MAKING TOO MUCH NOISE.

300
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:26,509
WELL, YOU'LL BE HAPPY TO KNOW

301
00:15:26,509 --> 00:15:28,511
I MOVED THE CAPTAIN'S CHAIR
DOWN TO ENGINEERING,

302
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:31,431
SO IT'S NICE AND QUIET
ON THE BRIDGE NOW.

303
00:15:31,431 --> 00:15:33,140
I PREFER TO WORK HERE.

304
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:40,273
I'LL NEED YOUR ASSISTANCE
WITH THIS.

305
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:42,817
WEREN'T YOU LISTENING TO ME?

306
00:15:42,817 --> 00:15:44,903
I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO CATER TO YOUR WHIMS.

307
00:15:44,903 --> 00:15:46,905
YOU WANT TO GET
YOUR NAME IMMORTALIZED IN

308
00:15:46,905 --> 00:15:50,241
THE VULCAN DATABASE, GET SOMEONE
ELSE TO HELP YOU DO IT.

309
00:15:50,241 --> 00:15:52,410
ARE YOU FEELING
ALL RIGHT, COMMANDER?

310
00:15:53,994 --> 00:15:56,038
I KNOW YOU DON'T THINK
THIS CHAIR IS IMPORTANT,

311
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:57,624
BUT YOU'RE WRONG.

312
00:15:57,624 --> 00:16:00,501
WHAT'S THE MOST CRITICAL
COMPONENT ON THIS SHIP?

313
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:02,670
THE MAIN COMPUTER?
THE WARP REACTOR?

314
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,672
HUNH-UH. IT'S THE CREW.

315
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,967
AND THE MOST IMPORTANT MEMBER
OF THE CREW IS THE CAPTAIN.

316
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:10,219
HE MAKES LIFE-AND-DEATH
DECISIONS EVERY DAY,

317
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,679
AND THE LAST THING HE
NEEDS TO BE THINKING

318
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,640
IN A CRITICAL SITUATION
IS, "GEE,

319
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:16,476
I WISH THIS CHAIR WASN'T
SUCH A PAIN IN THE ASS."

320
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:23,023
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

321
00:16:24,567 --> 00:16:26,569
-DOCTOR?
-SHH!

322
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:28,655
-WHEN ARE YOU GOING TO --
-WAIT!

323
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:34,368
I HAVE JUST ENOUGH TIME
TO SHOWER AND GET CHANGED.

324
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:36,329
I HAVEN'T DISCHARGED YOU,
ENSIGN.

325
00:16:36,329 --> 00:16:38,414
I -- I HAVEN'T SLEPT
ALL NIGHT AND I'M

326
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,416
SUPPOSED TO GO ON DUTY
IN 15 MINUTES.

327
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:43,085
I NEED TO PERFORM
A CEREBRAL MICRO-SECTION.

328
00:16:43,085 --> 00:16:45,254
A WHAT?

329
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:46,673
LIE DOWN.

330
00:16:48,215 --> 00:16:51,385
NO MORE TESTS.
I HAVE TO GET TO THE BRIDGE.

331
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,805
I'M GIVING YOU AN ORDER.

332
00:16:53,805 --> 00:16:56,265
IF I DON'T FINISH
THOSE UPGRADES,

333
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:57,600
I COULD GET A REPRIMAND.

334
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,352
IT'LL BE
IN MY PERMANENT RECORD.

335
00:16:59,352 --> 00:17:01,646
YOU HAVE FAR MORE TO WORRY ABOUT
THAN A BLEMISH ON YOUR RECORD.

336
00:17:01,646 --> 00:17:03,314
DO YOU SEE THERE?

337
00:17:03,314 --> 00:17:04,774
HMM?!

338
00:17:04,774 --> 00:17:06,818
YOUR CORTICAL SCAN SHOWS
ELEVATED LEVELS OF SEROTONIN

339
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:09,946
AND SEVERAL
OTHER NEUROTRANSMITTERS.

340
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:11,238
-WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
-I'LL LET YOU KNOW

341
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:13,867
ONCE I'VE COMPLETED
THE MICRO-SECTION.

342
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,369
CAN'T IT WAIT
UNTIL AFTER MY SHIFT?

343
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,287
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

344
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,707
IF THE CAPTAIN DOESN'T THINK
I CAN HANDLE MY DUTIES,

345
00:17:20,707 --> 00:17:22,792
I'LL BE SCRUBBING
PLASMA CONDUITS ON D-DECK

346
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:25,211
FOR THE NEXT FIVE YEARS.

347
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:27,421
I COULD BE COURT-MARTIALED.

348
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:30,257
AND WHAT IF YOU'RE CARRYING
A PROTOCYSTIAN SPORE,

349
00:17:30,257 --> 00:17:33,511
HMM, AND YOU INFECT
THE REST OF THE CREW?

350
00:17:33,511 --> 00:17:35,346
HOW WILL THAT REFLECT
ON YOU, HMM?

351
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:37,640
OR WHAT IF YOU SUDDENLY
SUFFER A SEIZURE AT THE HELM,

352
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,393
BECAUSE YOU'VE CONTRACTED
ANDRONESIAN ENCEPHALITIS?

353
00:17:40,393 --> 00:17:43,396
NOW, THERE IS SOMETHING
WRONG WITH YOU, ENSIGN,

354
00:17:43,396 --> 00:17:46,273
AND I INTEND TO FIND OUT
WHAT IT IS.

355
00:17:47,817 --> 00:17:50,194
NOT TODAY!
NOT DURING MY SHIFT!

356
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,530
UNLESS YOU'RE READY
TO TIE ME TO A BIO-BED,

357
00:17:52,530 --> 00:17:55,950
I'M GOING BACK TO MY HELM!

358
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:58,619
AT LEAST LET ME GIVE YOU
AN ANALGESIC

359
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:01,288
FOR THE HEADACHE, HMM?

360
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:05,125
WELL, THAT'S ALL I WANTED
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

361
00:18:10,965 --> 00:18:12,466
[ SIGHS ]

362
00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:15,511
IF IT GETS ANY WORSE OR
YOU SUFFER ANY OTHER SYMPTOMS,

363
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,931
RETURN HERE IMMEDIATELY.

364
00:18:23,603 --> 00:18:25,271
WHAT DID YOU...

365
00:18:37,742 --> 00:18:40,536
I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON THE NEW SECURITY PROTOCOL.

366
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:43,205
OBVIOUSLY, THE REACTOR MUST BE
SECURED IMMEDIATELY

367
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:44,832
DURING A TACTICAL ALERT.

368
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,793
"TACTICAL ALERT"?

369
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:49,003
I CONSIDERED YOUR SUGGESTION --
"REED ALERT" --

370
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:51,297
BUT, WELL,
IT SEEMED A BIT NARCISSISTIC.

371
00:18:51,297 --> 00:18:53,591
HAND ME THAT HYPERSPANNER,
WOULD YOU?

372
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:56,594
I'VE ALSO BEEN WORKING
ON A NEW ALERT SIGNAL.

373
00:18:56,594 --> 00:18:59,263
TELL ME WHAT YOU THINK.

374
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:02,850
[ ALARM WAILING ]

375
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:05,645
OR THIS ONE?

376
00:19:05,645 --> 00:19:08,106
[ ALARM BLARES ]

377
00:19:08,106 --> 00:19:10,108
[ BLARING STOPS ]

378
00:19:10,108 --> 00:19:11,734
WELL, WHICH DO YOU PREFER?

379
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:13,152
FOR WHAT?

380
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,113
A TACTICAL ALERT.

381
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:17,615
THEY BOTH SOUND LIKE
A BAG FULL OF CATS.

382
00:19:17,615 --> 00:19:19,826
WELL, THEY WERE DESIGNED
TO GET YOUR ATTENTION.

383
00:19:19,826 --> 00:19:22,954
I'LL LOOK THIS OVER
AND GET BACK TO YOU.

384
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,248
I ALSO NEED YOUR HELP

385
00:19:26,248 --> 00:19:29,794
ON AN EMERGENCY SHUTDOWN
PROCEDURE FOR THE E.P.S. GRID.

386
00:19:29,794 --> 00:19:33,380
I SAID...I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

387
00:19:35,174 --> 00:19:37,718
FINE. LET'S HOPE WE DON'T
SUFFER A CATASTROPHIC

388
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,804
REACTOR BREACH
IN THE MEANTIME.

389
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:42,598
MALCOLM...

390
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:45,059
ONE OF YOUR BOYS BORROWED
MY LASER MICROMETER.

391
00:19:45,059 --> 00:19:48,646
IF YOU'RE HEADING TO THE ARMORY,
COULD YOU GET IT BACK FOR ME?

392
00:19:57,030 --> 00:19:59,657
ENSIGN, IF WE DON'T
SERVE SOMETHING SOON,

393
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:02,368
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A RIOT
ON OUR HANDS.

394
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,620
IS THIS TOO SALTY?

395
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:10,751
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT.

396
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:13,379
HAND ME THE KREETASSAN SPICE.
I'LL ADD IT TO THE STOCK.

397
00:20:13,379 --> 00:20:14,672
OH, AND I'M OUT OF CARROTS.

398
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:16,632
-THERE ARE 25 PEOPLE WAITING --
-CARROTS!

399
00:20:22,513 --> 00:20:24,057
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

400
00:20:24,057 --> 00:20:26,600
YOU'VE BEEN COOKING THE SAME
MEAL OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

401
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:28,227
I BELIEVE I'M IN CHARGE
OF THE GALLEY.

402
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:30,229
-I UNDERSTAND THAT --
-YOU'RE RELIEVED.

403
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,522
MA'AM --

404
00:20:31,522 --> 00:20:33,566
GET OUT!

405
00:20:45,327 --> 00:20:47,914
LIEUTENANT, I NEED
YOUR ASSISTANCE FOR --

406
00:20:47,914 --> 00:20:50,541
CLEARANCE CODE?

407
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:52,334
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

408
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:54,670
WHAT IS YOUR CLEARANCE CODE?

409
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:58,465
THE ARMORY IS A RESTRICTED AREA.

410
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:02,178
EVEN TO THE FIRST OFFICER?

411
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:06,766
HOW DO I KNOW YOU ARE
THE FIRST OFFICER?

412
00:21:06,766 --> 00:21:10,228
WE'VE ENCOUNTERED SPECIES
THAT CAN ALTER THEIR APPEARANCE.

413
00:21:10,228 --> 00:21:12,063
THEY COULD MASQUERADE
AS ANY ONE OF US.

414
00:21:12,063 --> 00:21:14,774
I'VE ISSUED CODES
TO ALL SENIOR OFFICERS TO REVEAL

415
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:17,151
IF THE SHIP'S BEEN
INFILTRATED BY IMPOSTORS.

416
00:21:17,151 --> 00:21:19,319
PART OF YOUR NEW
SECURITY PROTOCOL?

417
00:21:19,319 --> 00:21:22,865
IT WAS SENT TO YOUR CONSOLE AS A
VOICE-ENCRYPTED COMMAND PACKET.

418
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,618
I HAVEN'T BEEN TO THE BRIDGE
FOR SEVERAL HOURS.

419
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:29,789
AS I WAS SAYING,
I NEED ASSISTANCE

420
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:31,999
ESTABLISHING A SENSOR INTERFACE
IN MY QUARTERS.

421
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:36,629
I HAVE ASKED COMMANDER TUCKER,
BUT HE BECAME...AGITATED.

422
00:21:36,629 --> 00:21:40,466
IT WAS UNCHARACTERISTIC,
EVEN FOR HIM.

423
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:45,429
HAVE YOU NOTICED ANYTHING
ABNORMAL ABOUT HIS BEHAVIOR?

424
00:21:45,429 --> 00:21:50,434
WHY DO YOU WANT TO ACCESS
THE SENSOR ARRAY...

425
00:21:50,434 --> 00:21:52,561
FROM YOUR QUARTERS?

426
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,272
I WAS ASKED
TO RUN DETAILED SCANS

427
00:21:54,272 --> 00:21:55,898
OF THE TRINARY STAR SYSTEM.

428
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:57,275
I WASN'T INFORMED.

429
00:21:57,275 --> 00:22:00,278
IT ISN'T A TACTICAL ISSUE.

430
00:22:00,278 --> 00:22:02,529
LIEUTENANT...

431
00:22:02,529 --> 00:22:04,615
WHY ARE YOU ARMED?

432
00:22:04,615 --> 00:22:06,575
FROM NOW ON,

433
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:08,619
SECURITY PERSONNEL ARE
TO WEAR SIDE ARMS

434
00:22:08,619 --> 00:22:10,913
IN ALL RESTRICTED AREAS.

435
00:22:10,913 --> 00:22:13,082
HAVE YOU CLEARED THIS
WITH THE CAPTAIN?

436
00:22:13,082 --> 00:22:14,792
IT'S IN MY PROPOSAL.

437
00:22:14,792 --> 00:22:16,335
HAS HE APPROVED YOUR PROPOSAL?

438
00:22:16,335 --> 00:22:18,587
I'VE BEEN TRYING TO GET HIM
TO PAY CLOSER ATTENTION

439
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:21,548
TO SECURITY SINCE WE
LEFT SPACEDOCK,

440
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:24,885
BUT HE'S MORE INTERESTED
IN FRATERNIZING WITH THE CREW,

441
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:28,514
INVITING THEM TO BREAKFAST
AND TO WATCH WATER POLO.

442
00:22:28,514 --> 00:22:32,143
I INTEND TO IMPLEMENT
SOME LONG-OVERDUE CHANGES,

443
00:22:32,143 --> 00:22:34,145
AND IF THE CAPTAIN
WON'T APPROVE THEM,

444
00:22:34,145 --> 00:22:36,689
THEN I'LL GO DIRECTLY
TO STARFLEET COMMAND.

445
00:22:38,149 --> 00:22:39,733
WAS THERE ANYTHING ELSE?

446
00:22:41,027 --> 00:22:42,320
NO.

447
00:22:44,238 --> 00:22:45,823
IT WASN'T LONG BEFORE I REALIZED

448
00:22:45,823 --> 00:22:48,909
THE ODD BEHAVIOR WASN'T LIMITED
TO COMMANDER TUCKER.

449
00:22:48,909 --> 00:22:52,872
IN FACT, EVERYONE I ENCOUNTERED
WAS ACTING STRANGELY,

450
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:57,877
GROWING CONSUMED WITH MATTERS
THAT SEEMED TRIVIAL, AT BEST.

451
00:22:57,877 --> 00:23:00,504
I ALSO DISCOVERED
THAT, ALTHOUGH I APPEARED

452
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:04,550
TO BE IMMUNE,
THE CAPTAIN WAS NOT.

453
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:14,894
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY CHAIR?

454
00:23:14,894 --> 00:23:17,730
DID YOU KNOW THAT THIS CHAIR
IS THE EXACT SAME MODEL

455
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:21,108
USED ON NEPTUNE-CLASS
SURVEY SHIPS?

456
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:23,319
IS THAT WHY YOU
CALLED ME DOWN HERE?

457
00:23:23,319 --> 00:23:27,365
<i>ENTERPRISE</i> IS THE FIRST WARP 5
VESSEL IN HUMAN HISTORY --

458
00:23:27,365 --> 00:23:30,034
THE PRIDE OF THE FLEET --
AND YOU'RE SITTING IN A CHAIR

459
00:23:30,034 --> 00:23:33,537
THEY'VE BEEN USING ON
WARP 2 SHIPS FOR OVER A DECADE.

460
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:36,123
YOU DESERVE BETTER,

461
00:23:36,123 --> 00:23:38,542
SO I'M STARTING FROM SCRATCH.

462
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:41,045
I'M GONNA BUILD YOU A THRONE.

463
00:23:41,045 --> 00:23:43,172
STAND RIGHT THERE.

464
00:23:44,464 --> 00:23:46,508
TUCKER: I NEED TO GET
A FEW PARAMETRIC SCANS

465
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:48,052
TO GET YOUR EXACT DIMENSIONS.

466
00:23:48,052 --> 00:23:51,429
THIS BABY'S GONNA FIT
LIKE A GLOVE.

467
00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:53,933
ISN'T THAT USED
FOR ALIGNING PHASE COILS?

468
00:23:53,933 --> 00:23:56,018
YOU WON'T FEEL A THING.

469
00:23:59,105 --> 00:24:02,775
LONG AS I'M DOWN HERE,
MAYBE I CAN GET YOUR OPINION.

470
00:24:02,775 --> 00:24:04,193
TUCKER: DON'T MOVE.

471
00:24:06,946 --> 00:24:09,949
"HOW DOES ONE MEASURE
A MAN'S LEGACY?

472
00:24:09,949 --> 00:24:12,410
"IS IT DEFINED BY
THE WORKS HE'S CREATED,

473
00:24:12,410 --> 00:24:14,412
"THE TECHNOLOGICAL
ADVANCES THAT WILL

474
00:24:14,412 --> 00:24:16,454
FOREVER ALTER THE COURSE
OF HUMAN HISTORY?"

475
00:24:16,454 --> 00:24:18,124
TURN AROUND.

476
00:24:19,457 --> 00:24:21,710
[ SIGHS ]
"IF SO,

477
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:24,046
"THEN NO MAN SINCE
ZEFRAM COCHRANE HIMSELF

478
00:24:24,046 --> 00:24:26,090
"HAS MADE A MORE
LASTING CONTRIBUTION

479
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:28,050
"TO THE FUTURE OF HUMANKIND

480
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:30,719
THAN MY FATHER,
DR. HENRY ARCHER."

481
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:32,554
ALL DONE.

482
00:24:34,140 --> 00:24:35,849
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

483
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:37,643
SOUNDS GOOD.

484
00:24:37,643 --> 00:24:39,437
LET ME READ YOU THE REST.

485
00:24:39,437 --> 00:24:41,814
I REALLY NEED TO GET
TO WORK ON THIS.

486
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:43,107
ARCHER: IT'S JUST
A FEW MORE PAGES.

487
00:24:43,107 --> 00:24:45,109
-HOW MANY MORE?
-19.

488
00:24:45,109 --> 00:24:47,069
19?

489
00:24:47,069 --> 00:24:49,405
ARE YOU WRITING THE PREFACE
OR THE BOOK?

490
00:24:49,405 --> 00:24:51,407
I'VE GOT A LOT TO SAY.

491
00:24:51,407 --> 00:24:53,367
NO KIDDING.

492
00:24:53,367 --> 00:24:56,036
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

493
00:24:56,036 --> 00:24:58,831
WELL, IF I MAY, SIR...

494
00:24:58,831 --> 00:25:01,125
IT'S A LITTLE LONGWINDED.

495
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,629
YOU'RE LUCKY
YOU'RE A DECENT ENGINEER,

496
00:25:05,629 --> 00:25:08,757
BECAUSE YOU OBVIOUSLY DON'T
KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT WRITING.

497
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:11,177
I'M NOT THE ONLY ONE.

498
00:25:16,682 --> 00:25:21,061
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

499
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:23,397
I HAVE 83 PEOPLE TO FEED,
NOT JUST SENIOR OFFICERS.

500
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:25,899
ALL I REQUESTED WAS A BOWL
OF<i> PLOMEEK</i> BROTH.

501
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:27,734
I DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR SPECIAL ORDERS.

502
00:25:27,734 --> 00:25:29,028
ANYWAY, YOU'LL
LIKE THIS BETTER.

503
00:25:29,028 --> 00:25:30,237
ARCHER: WHERE'S LUNCH?

504
00:25:30,237 --> 00:25:31,447
IT'LL BE READY
IN ONE MINUTE, SIR.

505
00:25:31,447 --> 00:25:32,781
I DON'T<i> HAVE</i> A MINUTE.

506
00:25:32,781 --> 00:25:34,074
IF YOU'RE SO HUNGRY,

507
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:35,868
FIX YOURSELF A SANDWICH.

508
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:37,911
[ CLATTERING ]

509
00:25:40,914 --> 00:25:43,541
CAPTAIN, MAY I SPEAK WITH YOU?

510
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:45,461
THAT IS A VERY COMPLEX RECIPE.

511
00:25:45,461 --> 00:25:47,338
I WILL NOT SERVE IT
TILL IT'S JUST RIGHT.

512
00:25:47,338 --> 00:25:50,049
MY FAMILY'S REPUTATION
IS AT STAKE!

513
00:25:50,049 --> 00:25:53,010
[ ALARM BLARES ]

514
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:54,761
<i>REED: THIS IS A TACTICAL ALERT.</i>

515
00:25:54,761 --> 00:25:57,348
<i>ALL HANDS REPORT</i>
<i>TO YOUR STATIONS.</i>

516
00:25:57,348 --> 00:25:58,598
[ LID THUMPS ]

517
00:25:58,598 --> 00:26:02,019
<i>I REPEAT --</i>
<i>THIS IS A TACTICAL ALERT.</i>

518
00:26:06,106 --> 00:26:08,108
[ ALARM BLARING ]

519
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:09,402
REPORT!

520
00:26:09,402 --> 00:26:12,071
THE CREW'S RESPONSE
WAS UNACCEPTABLE.

521
00:26:12,071 --> 00:26:14,614
38% OF THEM FAILED TO REPORT
TO THEIR STATIONS.

522
00:26:14,614 --> 00:26:16,409
CRITICAL SYSTEMS
HAVEN'T BEEN SECURED.

523
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:17,868
I HAVEN'T EVEN HEARD
FROM ENGINEERING.

524
00:26:17,868 --> 00:26:20,829
SHUT OFF THAT DAMN NOISE!
SHUT IT OFF!

525
00:26:20,829 --> 00:26:23,249
I DON'T RECALL AUTHORIZING
A TACTICAL DRILL.

526
00:26:23,249 --> 00:26:24,875
WELL, IT WOULDN'T BE
MUCH OF A DRILL

527
00:26:24,875 --> 00:26:27,753
IF EVERYBODY KNEW
ABOUT IT,<i> SIR.</i>

528
00:26:27,753 --> 00:26:29,547
ONE MINUTE AND 15 SECONDS.

529
00:26:29,547 --> 00:26:31,424
-WHAT?
-IT TOOK YOU

530
00:26:31,424 --> 00:26:34,760
ONE MINUTE AND 15 SECONDS
TO REACH YOUR POST.

531
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,012
I'D EXPECT MORE
OF OUR COMMANDING OFFICER,

532
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:39,265
GIVEN THAT THE CREW
JUST MIGHT FOLLOW HIS EXAMPLE.

533
00:26:39,265 --> 00:26:41,100
CAPTAIN?

534
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:44,186
REED: ONE MINUTE AND<i> 49</i> SECONDS.

535
00:26:44,186 --> 00:26:46,897
YOU MIGHT WANT TO SEE THIS, SIR.

536
00:26:46,897 --> 00:26:50,067
INTERACTIVE STATUS DISPLAYS,
SECONDARY HELM CONTROL.

537
00:26:50,067 --> 00:26:52,069
IT'S EVEN GOT
INERTIAL MICRO-DAMPERS.

538
00:26:52,069 --> 00:26:55,072
THE SHIP COULD BE SHAKING APART,
AND YOU'D HARDLY FEEL A THING.

539
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:57,699
REED: YOU IGNORED
A TACTICAL ALERT FOR THIS?!

540
00:26:57,699 --> 00:27:00,119
I WANT TO RUN SOME COLORS
BY YOU FOR THE HEADREST.

541
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:02,079
REED: THIS IS ALL
A BIG JOKE TO YOU!

542
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:03,289
GIVE IT A REST!

543
00:27:03,289 --> 00:27:05,332
THIS ISN'T A BLOODY
PLEASURE CRUISE!

544
00:27:05,332 --> 00:27:07,418
WITHOUT PROPER DISCIPLINE
ON THIS SHIP,

545
00:27:07,418 --> 00:27:08,961
THIS MISSION IS DOOMED!

546
00:27:08,961 --> 00:27:11,589
TUCKER: WHY DON'T YOU GO PLAY
SOLDIER SOMEWHERE ELSE?

547
00:27:11,589 --> 00:27:14,049
REED: IF THIS WERE
A MILITARY SITUATION,

548
00:27:14,049 --> 00:27:16,051
YOU'D BE TAKEN OUT AND SHOT.

549
00:27:18,011 --> 00:27:20,431
HEY! HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY!

550
00:27:20,431 --> 00:27:22,099
I DON'T CARE WHAT COLOR
THE HEADREST IS

551
00:27:22,099 --> 00:27:23,476
OR WHETHER IT CAN
SERVE ME ICED TEA!

552
00:27:23,476 --> 00:27:25,144
I JUST WANT A PLACE TO SIT
WHEN I'M ON DUTY.

553
00:27:25,144 --> 00:27:27,354
AND IF I HEAR THAT ALARM
ONE MORE TIME,

554
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:30,441
I MAY HAVE YOU TAKEN OUT
AND SHOT.

555
00:27:33,735 --> 00:27:35,904
UNLESS THERE'S
A<i> REAL</i> EMERGENCY --

556
00:27:35,904 --> 00:27:37,490
LIKE A REACTOR BREACH --

557
00:27:37,490 --> 00:27:39,116
I DON'T WANT TO BE DISTURBED.

558
00:27:40,326 --> 00:27:43,579
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

559
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:52,670
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

560
00:27:52,670 --> 00:27:54,507
GO AWAY.

561
00:27:57,092 --> 00:27:59,136
DO I HAVE TO START
LOCKING MY DOOR?

562
00:27:59,136 --> 00:28:01,555
YOU SAID TO INTERRUPT YOU

563
00:28:01,555 --> 00:28:03,182
IF THERE WAS AN EMERGENCY.

564
00:28:03,182 --> 00:28:04,766
I BELIEVE THERE IS.

565
00:28:04,766 --> 00:28:06,684
IS THAT RIGHT?

566
00:28:06,684 --> 00:28:09,896
THE CREW'S BEHAVIOR
HAS BECOME ERRATIC...

567
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,483
EVEN BY HUMAN STANDARDS.

568
00:28:12,483 --> 00:28:15,110
THEY'VE GROWN DISTRACTED.

569
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,112
EVERYONE I'VE ENCOUNTERED

570
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:19,990
APPEARS TO BE PREOCCUPIED
WITH TRIVIAL MATTERS...

571
00:28:19,990 --> 00:28:22,368
[ BEEPING ]

572
00:28:22,368 --> 00:28:25,078
ENSIGN SATO'S RECIPE,
FOR EXAMPLE...

573
00:28:26,497 --> 00:28:28,040
YOUR PREFACE.

574
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:30,042
WE SHOULD DECLARE
A MEDICAL EMERGENCY

575
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:31,669
AND HAVE DR. PHLOX
EXAMINE THE CREW.

576
00:28:31,669 --> 00:28:33,587
I SUGGEST
HE BEGIN WITH YOU.

577
00:28:44,931 --> 00:28:46,642
I'M BUSY.

578
00:28:49,436 --> 00:28:51,438
-CAPTAIN.
-DISMISSED.

579
00:28:51,438 --> 00:28:53,607
-YOUR CREW IS IN DANGER.
-I GAVE YOU AN ORDER.

580
00:28:53,607 --> 00:28:54,858
CAPTAIN --

581
00:28:54,858 --> 00:28:56,860
I SUGGEST YOU FOLLOW IT

582
00:28:56,860 --> 00:28:59,905
OR I'LL HAVE YOU CONFINED
TO YOUR QUARTERS

583
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:04,326
UNTIL...UNTIL A VULCAN SHIP
CAN COME AND GET YOU.

584
00:29:20,092 --> 00:29:23,095
OH, YOU'RE JUST IN TIME,
SUBCOMMANDER.

585
00:29:23,095 --> 00:29:25,764
THERE'S A SURGICAL GOWN IN THE
COMPARTMENT BY THE MICROSCOPE.

586
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:29,435
HEH! THIS IS A RARE OPPORTUNITY
TO EXPLORE THE HUMAN BRAIN.

587
00:29:29,435 --> 00:29:31,395
WAS HE INJURED?

588
00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:33,397
HEADACHE. HEH!
AT FIRST, I THOUGHT

589
00:29:33,397 --> 00:29:35,441
IT WAS A SIMPLE
VASCULAR DILATION,

590
00:29:35,441 --> 00:29:38,235
BUT THEN I DISCOVERED...

591
00:29:38,235 --> 00:29:41,614
A CHEMICAL IMBALANCE
IN HIS PREFRONTAL CORTEX.

592
00:29:41,614 --> 00:29:44,324
I'M GOING TO BEGIN BY
EXTRACTING THE FIRST

593
00:29:44,324 --> 00:29:47,327
12 MILLIMETERS
OF HIS PARIETAL LOBE.

594
00:29:47,327 --> 00:29:49,538
A SUBCELLULAR ANALYSIS
OF THE TISSUE

595
00:29:49,538 --> 00:29:51,624
SHOULD SHED SOME LIGHT
ON THE MYSTERY.

596
00:29:51,624 --> 00:29:54,627
DOCTOR, YOU MAY WANT TO DELAY
THE PROCEDURE.

597
00:29:54,627 --> 00:29:56,378
WE HAVE A LARGER PROBLEM.

598
00:29:56,378 --> 00:29:58,547
THE ENTIRE CREW IS ILL.

599
00:29:59,839 --> 00:30:01,800
THEY'LL HAVE TO WAIT.

600
00:30:07,514 --> 00:30:09,558
YOU'VE BEEN AFFECTED AS WELL.

601
00:30:09,558 --> 00:30:12,227
PLEASE REMOVE YOUR HAND.

602
00:30:15,021 --> 00:30:17,733
I WON'T ASK YOU AGAIN.

603
00:30:22,571 --> 00:30:25,324
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN I'VE COMPLETED THE SURGERY.

604
00:30:25,324 --> 00:30:27,075
MMM!

605
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:27,553
THE CREW'S BIO-SIGNS
WERE GROWING ERRATIC.

606
00:31:27,553 --> 00:31:29,429
I BEGAN TO DOUBT ANY OF THEM
WOULD SURVIVE

607
00:31:29,429 --> 00:31:30,972
MORE THAN A FEW HOURS.

608
00:31:30,972 --> 00:31:33,183
IRONICALLY,
DR. PHLOX'S OBSESSION WITH

609
00:31:33,183 --> 00:31:36,228
ENSIGN MAYWEATHER'S HEADACHE
HAS PROVIDED SOME USEFUL DATA.

610
00:31:36,228 --> 00:31:38,856
HIS CEREBRAL SCANS
HAVE HELPED ME DETERMINE

611
00:31:38,856 --> 00:31:41,525
THAT THE RADIATION COMING FROM
THE TRINARY SYSTEM IS CAUSING --

612
00:31:41,525 --> 00:31:43,276
[ BEEPING ]

613
00:31:43,276 --> 00:31:46,363
COMPUTER, PAUSE.

614
00:31:47,947 --> 00:31:50,950
COMPUTER, RESUME LOG.
[ BEEPS ]

615
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:53,370
MY RADIOMETRIC ANALYSIS
IS COMPLETE.

616
00:31:53,370 --> 00:31:56,164
AS I SUSPECTED,
REVERSING COURSE

617
00:31:56,164 --> 00:31:58,792
WON'T TAKE US OUT OF DANGER
QUICKLY ENOUGH.

618
00:31:58,792 --> 00:32:00,794
THE RADIATION APPEARS
TO EXTEND OUTWARD

619
00:32:00,794 --> 00:32:03,797
AT LEAST HALF A LIGHT-YEAR
IN EVERY DIRECTION EXCEPT ONE.

620
00:32:03,797 --> 00:32:06,216
IF I CAN CHART A COURSE
BETWEEN THE STARS,

621
00:32:06,216 --> 00:32:09,511
WE COULD ESCAPE THE RADIATION
BEFORE THE CREW SUCCUMBS.

622
00:32:09,511 --> 00:32:13,306
BUT I WON'T BE ABLE TO PILOT
THE SHIP ALONE.

623
00:32:15,851 --> 00:32:17,477
CAPTAIN?

624
00:32:17,477 --> 00:32:19,145
CAPTAIN ARCHER!

625
00:32:20,689 --> 00:32:22,399
YOU'RE NEEDED ON THE BRIDGE.

626
00:32:22,399 --> 00:32:24,359
I TOLD YOU NOT TO DISTURB ME.

627
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:26,319
WE HAVE VERY LITTLE TIME.

628
00:32:26,319 --> 00:32:28,988
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
-YOUR CREW MAY BE DYING.

629
00:32:28,988 --> 00:32:30,866
WHAT?

630
00:32:30,866 --> 00:32:33,744
DO YOU REMEMBER
THAT TRINARY STAR SYSTEM?

631
00:32:33,744 --> 00:32:35,454
THE ONE WITH THE BLACK HOLE?

632
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:38,582
IT'S EMITTING A DANGEROUS FORM
OF RADIATION.

633
00:32:39,917 --> 00:32:42,544
IT'S AFFECTING
YOUR PREFRONTAL CORTEX.

634
00:32:42,544 --> 00:32:44,588
I BELIEVE THAT'S WHY
YOU AND THE CREW

635
00:32:44,588 --> 00:32:47,006
HAVE BEEN EXHIBITING
OBSESSIVE BEHAVIOR.

636
00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:48,675
[ GRUNTS ]

637
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:54,139
SOME OF THE CREW'S BIO-SIGNS
ARE ALREADY UNSTABLE.

638
00:32:54,139 --> 00:32:56,600
IF YOU'RE EXPOSED
TO THE RADIATION MUCH LONGER,

639
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:59,018
YOU WON'T SURVIVE.

640
00:32:59,018 --> 00:33:00,687
[ GROANING ]

641
00:33:13,659 --> 00:33:16,369
DO YOU UNDERSTAND
WHAT I'M TELLING YOU?

642
00:33:16,369 --> 00:33:18,079
TURN IT OFF.

643
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:20,081
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

644
00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:23,126
YES...RADIATION.

645
00:33:24,586 --> 00:33:26,588
TELL...PHLOX.

646
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:29,883
IF...THE CREW IS SICK...

647
00:33:31,217 --> 00:33:32,845
TELL PHLOX.

648
00:33:32,845 --> 00:33:34,888
HE'S BEEN AFFECTED AS WELL.

649
00:33:36,222 --> 00:33:37,516
BUT NOT YOU?

650
00:33:37,516 --> 00:33:40,393
VULCAN PHYSIOLOGY
SEEMS TO BE IMMUNE.

651
00:33:40,393 --> 00:33:43,730
BRING US ABOUT.

652
00:33:43,730 --> 00:33:46,399
TURN THE SHIP AROUND.

653
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:57,369
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

654
00:33:57,369 --> 00:33:59,287
IF WE GO BACK THE WAY WE CAME,

655
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:01,957
WE'LL SPEND TWO MORE DAYS
IN THE RADIATION FIELD.

656
00:34:03,291 --> 00:34:05,251
[ GROANS ]

657
00:34:05,251 --> 00:34:07,212
I'VE CHARTED A COURSE

658
00:34:07,212 --> 00:34:10,298
THAT'LL HAVE US CLEAR
OF THE RADIATION

659
00:34:10,298 --> 00:34:12,926
IN LESS THAN 17 MINUTES.

660
00:34:12,926 --> 00:34:15,053
LOUSY COFFEE.

661
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:16,889
BUT WE'LL HAVE TO PASS

662
00:34:16,889 --> 00:34:19,975
WITHIN 2 MILLION KILOMETERS
OF THE BLACK HOLE.

663
00:34:19,975 --> 00:34:24,730
THERE'S CONSIDERABLE DEBRIS
AND GRAVITATIONAL SHEAR.

664
00:34:27,566 --> 00:34:29,568
SOMEONE NEEDS
TO PILOT<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

665
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:31,987
WHILE I DETERMINE
THE COURSE CORRECTIONS.

666
00:34:31,987 --> 00:34:34,364
[ GRUNTS ]

667
00:34:34,364 --> 00:34:35,949
TRAVIS?

668
00:34:35,949 --> 00:34:37,910
HE'S BEEN SEDATED.

669
00:34:41,204 --> 00:34:43,874
I'M IN NO CONDITION TO...

670
00:34:43,874 --> 00:34:46,376
FLY...A STARSHIP.

671
00:34:46,376 --> 00:34:49,295
WE HAVE NO OTHER CHOICE.

672
00:35:04,394 --> 00:35:06,063
[ RUMBLING ]

673
00:35:07,606 --> 00:35:09,983
T'POL: MORE GRAVITATIONAL SHEAR.

674
00:35:09,983 --> 00:35:11,985
WE'RE TOO FAR TO PORT.

675
00:35:11,985 --> 00:35:15,655
ARCHER: BUT YOU SAID
BEARING 2.4.

676
00:35:15,655 --> 00:35:17,574
12.4.

677
00:35:17,574 --> 00:35:19,576
MY MISTAKE.

678
00:35:19,576 --> 00:35:21,536
[ GRUNTING ]

679
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:26,249
12.4. YEAH.

680
00:35:28,668 --> 00:35:30,796
HOW MUCH LONGER
IS THIS GONNA TAKE?

681
00:35:32,672 --> 00:35:34,091
SIX MINUTES.

682
00:35:34,091 --> 00:35:36,301
ARCHER: I'M GOOD FOR THAT.

683
00:35:36,301 --> 00:35:38,053
ANOTHER SHEAR FRONT.

684
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:40,931
YOU NEED TO ROTATE
OUR LONGITUDINAL AXIS

685
00:35:40,931 --> 00:35:42,515
BY 12 DEGREES

686
00:35:42,515 --> 00:35:46,812
AND BRING OUR FLIGHT VECTOR
TO 014 MARK 27.

687
00:35:46,812 --> 00:35:49,188
HOLD ON. HOLD ON.
ZERO WHAT?

688
00:35:49,188 --> 00:35:51,650
T'POL: 014 MARK --

689
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:53,652
MARK 27.

690
00:35:53,652 --> 00:35:55,821
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

691
00:35:58,073 --> 00:35:59,741
[ THUDDING ]

692
00:36:01,284 --> 00:36:05,288
T'POL: JUST MINOR DEBRIS.
THE HULL PLATING IS HOLDING.

693
00:36:05,288 --> 00:36:08,959
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]
OUR LATERAL VECTOR IS DRIFTING.

694
00:36:08,959 --> 00:36:10,961
CAPTAIN!

695
00:36:10,961 --> 00:36:14,172
HANG ON A SECOND.

696
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:18,844
I FEEL LIKE
I'M IN...FLIGHT SCHOOL AGAIN.

697
00:36:18,844 --> 00:36:20,887
YOU'RE DOING WELL.

698
00:36:20,887 --> 00:36:22,889
NEW HEADING.

699
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:26,893
006 MARK 4.

700
00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:28,937
6...

701
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:35,568
[ ALARM BLARING ]
CAPTAIN!

702
00:36:35,568 --> 00:36:37,529
I SEE IT.

703
00:36:45,704 --> 00:36:47,455
WE NEED PHASE CANNONS.

704
00:36:47,455 --> 00:36:49,499
THEY'D TAKE TOO LONG TO CHARGE.

705
00:36:53,003 --> 00:36:55,005
[ THUDS ]

706
00:36:55,005 --> 00:36:57,632
[ ALARM BLARES ]

707
00:36:57,632 --> 00:37:00,844
ALL WEAPONS ARE ONLINE.

708
00:37:00,844 --> 00:37:02,929
IT MUST BE PART
OF THE NEW SECURITY PROTOCOL.

709
00:37:02,929 --> 00:37:05,348
FIRE!

710
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:13,899
[ GRUNTING ]

711
00:37:18,528 --> 00:37:20,279
[ ALARM BLARING ]

712
00:37:21,990 --> 00:37:24,034
COULD YOU SHUT THAT OFF?

713
00:37:26,369 --> 00:37:28,955
[ BLARING STOPS ]

714
00:37:28,955 --> 00:37:30,999
HOW MUCH LONGER?

715
00:37:32,333 --> 00:37:35,087
LESS THAN 10 SECONDS.

716
00:37:38,464 --> 00:37:40,926
5 MORE SECONDS.

717
00:37:49,809 --> 00:37:51,811
ANY MORE SURPRISES?

718
00:37:51,811 --> 00:37:54,272
NOTHING ON SENSORS.

719
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:07,202
[ GROANS ]

720
00:38:07,202 --> 00:38:10,247
DID WE GET SOME NICE PICTURES
OF THE BLACK HOLE?

721
00:38:25,137 --> 00:38:26,763
HOW ARE YOU FEELING?

722
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:29,808
A LITTLE TIRED,
BUT THE HEADACHE'S GONE.

723
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:31,434
WHAT'D YOU DO?

724
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:33,812
VERY LITTLE...FORTUNATELY.

725
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:35,772
YOU'RE, UH, FREE TO GO.

726
00:38:37,398 --> 00:38:39,276
CAPTAIN.

727
00:38:41,611 --> 00:38:43,155
HOW'S THE CREW?

728
00:38:43,155 --> 00:38:45,282
OH, I'M CONTINUING TO MONITOR
VITAL SIGNS,

729
00:38:45,282 --> 00:38:49,244
BUT I'VE DETECTED NO LINGERING
EFFECTS FROM THE RADIATION.

730
00:38:49,244 --> 00:38:50,912
MOSTLY JUST RATTLED NERVES,

731
00:38:50,912 --> 00:38:52,538
A FEW BRUISES AND SPRAINS

732
00:38:52,538 --> 00:38:56,084
FROM WHEN SOME OF THEM
LOST CONSCIOUSNESS.

733
00:38:56,084 --> 00:38:58,377
I APPRECIATE YOUR INTERVENING,

734
00:38:58,377 --> 00:39:02,882
UH, BEFORE I GOT ANY FURTHER
WITH MR. MAYWEATHER'S PROCEDURE.

735
00:39:02,882 --> 00:39:05,969
I WASN'T CERTAIN
IT WOULD WORK ON A DENOBULAN.

736
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:07,762
IT WORKED QUITE EFFECTIVELY,
I CAN ASSURE YOU.

737
00:39:07,762 --> 00:39:11,308
W-WHAT PROCEDURE
ON MR. MAYWEATHER?

738
00:39:11,308 --> 00:39:14,269
THE RADIATION AFFECTED MY
NERVOUS SYSTEM RATHER SEVERELY.

739
00:39:14,269 --> 00:39:15,645
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

740
00:39:15,645 --> 00:39:17,314
-I'LL BE WITH YOU IN A MOMENT.
-OKAY, DOCTOR.

741
00:39:17,314 --> 00:39:18,690
I'LL PROVIDE YOU
WITH A FULL REPORT

742
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:21,109
WHEN I'VE FINISHED
TREATING THE CREW.

743
00:39:26,405 --> 00:39:28,491
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME, CAPTAIN?

744
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:30,285
I DID.

745
00:39:33,205 --> 00:39:37,250
WHEN T'POL AND I WERE NAVIGATING
THE DEBRIS FIELD,

746
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:40,503
YOUR TACTICAL ALERT WENT OFF.

747
00:39:40,503 --> 00:39:41,796
I HEARD, SIR.

748
00:39:41,796 --> 00:39:44,757
I'VE ALREADY DEACTIVATED
THE NEW PROTOCOLS.

749
00:39:45,758 --> 00:39:47,719
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

750
00:39:47,719 --> 00:39:52,682
THEY BROUGHT THE WEAPONS ONLINE
RIGHT WHEN WE NEEDED THEM.

751
00:39:52,682 --> 00:39:55,101
IF YOU HAVE NO OBJECTION,

752
00:39:55,101 --> 00:39:59,105
I'D LIKE TO MAKE IT
STANDARD PROCEDURE.

753
00:39:59,105 --> 00:40:01,149
NO OBJECTION, SIR.

754
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:08,114
YOU STILL NEED TO WORK
ON THAT ALARM.

755
00:40:08,114 --> 00:40:10,867
I'LL GET RIGHT ON IT.

756
00:40:20,085 --> 00:40:23,296
DOESN'T LOOK
ANY DIFFERENT TO ME.

757
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:25,131
GIVE IT A TRY.

758
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:35,392
[ SIGHS ]

759
00:40:35,392 --> 00:40:37,602
HMM.

760
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:44,984
FEELS BETTER.
WHAT DID YOU DO?

761
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,569
CROSS YOUR LEGS.

762
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:56,788
WHAT DID YOU DO?
SEEMS TOTALLY DIFFERENT.

763
00:40:56,788 --> 00:40:58,957
I LOWERED IT...

764
00:41:00,208 --> 00:41:01,667
BY ONE CENTIMETER.

765
00:41:01,667 --> 00:41:05,463
[ CHUCKLES ]
THAT'S ALL?

766
00:41:05,463 --> 00:41:08,507
DIDN'T HAVE TIME TO INSTALL
THE NEW STATUS DISPLAYS

767
00:41:08,507 --> 00:41:11,136
OR THE INERTIAL
MICRO-DAMPERS, BUT, UH,

768
00:41:11,136 --> 00:41:13,221
IF YOU GIVE ME
A COUPLE OF DAYS...

769
00:41:13,221 --> 00:41:16,682
I THINK THIS WILL BE FINE,
COMMANDER. THANKS.

770
00:41:16,682 --> 00:41:18,935
HOW ABOUT I JUST ATTACH
THE CUP HOLDER?

771
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:20,353
THIS'LL BE FINE.

772
00:41:46,045 --> 00:41:48,298
HOW DOES THIS SOUND?
